{"name":"sp_portal","description":"Customizable web interface for users to interact with the ServiceNow platform.","summary":"In ServiceNow, the `{sp_portal}` object is utilized within the Service Portal framework. The Service Portal is a user-friendly interface designed to offer a streamlined and customizable experience for end-users interacting with various services and resources on the ServiceNow platform.\n\nKey features and functionalities of `{sp_portal}` include:\n\n1. **Customization**: Allows for extensive customization of the portal's look and feel using widgets, themes, and custom scripts.\n2. **Widgets**: Building blocks of the portal pages, which can be reused and configured to display dynamic content.\n3. **Pages**: Composed of one or more widgets, these pages serve as the primary interface for users to interact with the portal.\n4. **Themes**: Control the overall styling and branding of the portal, including colors, fonts, and layout.\n5. **Service Catalog**: Integration with the Service Catalog allows users to request services, report issues, and access knowledge articles.\n6. **User Experience**: Enhances user experience by providing a responsive and intuitive interface that adapts to various devices and screen sizes.\n7. **Security**: Ensures secure access and data privacy through role-based access controls and other security features.\n\nOverall, `{sp_portal}` in ServiceNow is designed to deliver a cohesive, efficient, and personalized user experience, facilitating better service delivery and user satisfaction.","attributes":[{"name":"sp_rectangle_menu","type":"reference"},{"name":"icon","type":"user_image"},{"name":"search_results_configuration","type":"reference"},{"name":"sc_catalog","type":"reference"},{"name":"sys_updated_on","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"title","type":"translated_text"},{"name":"ts_index_group","type":"reference"},{"name":"dark_theme","type":"reference"},{"name":"sc_catalog_page","type":"reference"},{"name":"sys_class_n